You have set the `target` attribute (incorrectly). The default value for target is `_self`, which is what you actually want and in that case you can also remove the whole attribute from the link. 

    &lt;a href=&quot;file:^px/Home.px&quot;&gt;&lt;img id=&quot;clickHome&quot; src=&quot;images/btnHome.png&quot; title=&quot;Home&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

or also correct

    &lt;a href=&quot;file:^px/Home.px&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;&lt;img id=&quot;clickHome&quot; src=&quot;images/btnHome.png&quot; title=&quot;Home&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;

The target attribute specifies where to open the linked document:

&gt; `_blank` - opens the linked document in a new window or tab  
&gt;
&gt; `_self` - opens the linked document in the same frame as it was clicked (this is default)  
&gt;
&gt; `_parent` - opens the linked document in the parent frame
&gt;
&gt; `_top` - opens the linked document in the full body of the window 
&gt; 
&gt; `framename` opens the linked document in the named iframe/window

Read more about the target attribute:  
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a?retiredLocale=de#attributes  
https://www.w3schools.com/tags/att_a_target.asp

