I am migrating an application to Spring Security 6 and I have an odd problem. Our app authenticates users externally via a cookie key (it is an internal app and that is how our security system functions) and we have two security configurations, API and Web. 

In previous versions of Spring Security when an attempt was made to access a secured API resource, the service would enter an `ApiAuthorizationErrorHandler` which would return a 401 unauthorized if credentials were not found or 403 forbidden if some other exception occurred. 

