As you&#39;ll find if you read in the migration guide for Hibernate 6, we no longer use stringly-typed names to identify types. Which is much better.

But even better still, you no longer need a custom `@Type` annotation to persist `UUID`s. So:

```java
@Id
private UUID id;
```

would in principle work fine.

You can even use:

```java
@Id @GeneratedValue
private UUID id;
```

if you want the `UUID` to be generated.

However, note that, by default, this maps to a column of type `UUID` if the database has such a type. If you really need to map to a `VARCHAR` columns, use:

```java
@Id @GeneratedValue
@JdbcTypeCode(Types.VARCHAR)
private UUID id;
```

or:

```java
@Id @GeneratedValue
@JdbcType(VarcharJdbcType.class)
private UUID id;
```

depending on taste.

